Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, Wednesday, commiserated with the family of the mother and three daughters who died on Tuesday night in a fire disaster at Red Bricks Quarters on Maiduguri road, Damaturu in Yobe State. Lawan also commended the head of the family who bravely rescued his five-year-old son before escaping from the inferno. Special Adviser on Media to the Senate President, Ola Awoniyi said this in a statement in Abuja. The Senate President also condoled with the government and people of Yobe State over the tragic incident. He further enjoined the people to take seriously tips for prevention of fire disaster in homes and offices, especially whenever there is a power outage. But he, however, prayed for Allahâ€™s comfort for the bereaved family and for an end to such incidents.